result.name: Taylor Shellfish Farms

reviews.text: This place isn’t cheap. But loved the late night oyster and wine with my friends. They do offer a good selection of oysters from the US, AUSTRALIA, Japan, etc. I would definitely come back again.
Good food, good service, space a bit tight

Found out about this place through a food expo and decided to try it out. One of the major importers of oysters in Hong Kong and the supplier for one of Hong Kong's high end supermarket/department store AEON, we were excited to try out its 20+ choices in shellfish. Still liked the French Bellon the most (even though it is rather pricey). The underlying sulphuric taste immediately took us back to an oyster tasting session in Leon, France!

We are from Washington state where we visit the original Taylor's often, this location did a good job of representing the company. The manager was very friendly and chatted with us about where each oysters were from. The food and oyster selection especially was unparalleled. Highly recommend this place for a taste of the ocean! The Puget Sound oysters are still our favorite with the best merroir!!!
Great. Indian lady chef's taste and assortment was nice.
